 1  
Social Identity and Preferences 
by  Daniel J. Benjamin, James J. Choi, and A. Joshua Strickland 
 
Data and Analysis Programs 
 
I. Experiment 1 
 
Experiment1_Variables.do.  Converts raw data in Experiment1.dta into processed dataset 
Experiment1_Variables.dta containing variables used in analysis for Experiment 1 (to be run 
before Experiment1_Claims.do and Table1-2.do).  
Experiment1_Claims.do.  Provides supporting evidence for empirical claims made in body 
of paper concerning Experiment 1. 
Table1.do.  Calculates percentages of impatient and safe choices for Table 1. 
Table2.do.  Calculates ethnicity-salience treatment effects for Table 2. 
 
II. Experiment 2 
 
Experiment2_Variables.do. Converts Experiment2_Temple.dta and Experiment2_UM.dta 
into Experiment2_Variables.dta containing variables used in analysis for Experiment 2 (to be 
run before Experiment2_Claims.do and Table3-5.do). 
Experiment2_Claims.do.  Provides supporting evidence for empirical claims made in body 
of paper concerning Experiment 2.  
Table3.do.  Calculates percentages of impatient and safe choices for Table 3. 
Table4.do.  Calculates baseline identity-salience treatment effects for Table 4. 
Table5.do.  Calculates baseline identity-salience treatment effects for Table 5. 
AppendixTable1.do . Calculates summary statistics for Appendix Table 1. 
 
 
Description of Variables in Programs 
 
I. Experiment 1 
 
A. Raw Data 
 
The file Experiment1.dta contains the responses of participants in Experiment 1. The variables 
are defined as follows. 
 
Identifying Information 
 
id. ID number uniquely identifying subjects in Experiment 1. 
qnaire.  Experimental condition (1 – control, 2 – ethnicity-salience). 
rubric.  Question order (for details, see time1-22smaller , time23-46larger , and risk47-64 ). 
date.  Date when questionnaire completed. 
 
